
The CI workflow runs this automatically on every push and pull request.

### Vulnerability threshold

The CI fails on high-severity vulnerabilities. Medium and low severity issues are reported but don't fail the build.

### Handling false positives

If `pip-audit` reports a false positive:
1. Check the vulnerability details
2. If it doesn't affect your code, add an ignore flag to the CI command
3. Document the reason in `docs/DEPENDENCY_AUDIT.md`

## Code standards

- Follow existing code style
- Add tests for new functionality
- Update documentation as needed
- Ensure CI passes before merging
